    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6224" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μηρός</span></b> : <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">ham</span>,
          upper part of the <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">thigh;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μηρὼ πλήσσεσθαι</span>, to ‘smite the
          thighs,’ a gesture indicative of surprise or other excitement, <i><span class="en">Il. 12.162</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            16.125</span></i>; of victims, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μηροὺς
            ἐξέταμον</span>, i. e. cut out the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μηρία</span> from the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μηροί, Α
            460</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
          12.360</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
